# Image Upload and Retrieval API

This project provides a simple API for handling image uploads and retrievals. It includes two main endpoints:

1. **POST /upload:** Upload an image, process it, and save it to a MongoDB database.
2. **GET /get_image/:id:** Retrieve a saved image from the database using its secure URL.

## Introduction

This project aims to simplify the process of handling image uploads and retrievals through a RESTful API. It leverages Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and Multer to provide a straightforward solution for storing and retrieving images securely.

## Features

- Image upload and processing.
- Secure retrieval of saved images through unique URLs.
- MongoDB integration for data storage.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- [MongoDB](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community)

